The problem is that he wants a national 15 dollar minimum wage. While some 
areas like San Francisco, have very high costs of living, other areas such 
as rural Mississippi have much lower costs of living. What most economists 
want to do is to abolish/have a very low national minimum wage and allow 
individual municipalities to enact their own minimum wage. This way, people 
in high cost of living areas will get the money they need to survive, while 
people in places with a lower cost of living will not need to face 
increased unemployment. My point is that, although some places may need a 
$15/hour minimum wage or even a $20/hour minimum wage, other places do not. 
Minimum wages should reflect the living wage of the area, which differs 
across the US.﻿

want to do is to abolish/have a very low national minimum wage and allow 
individual municipalities to enact their own minimum wage. This way, people 
in high cost of living areas will get the money they need to survive, while 
people in places with a lower cost of living will not need to face 
increased unemployment. My point is that, although some places may need a 
$15/hour minimum wage or even a $20/hour minimum wage, other places do not.

across the US.
